.TH XkbAddGeomColor 3 "libX11 1.6.1" "X Version 11" "XKB FUNCTIONS"
.SH NAME
XkbAddGeomColor \-  Add one color name ta a existin keyboard geometry 
description
.SH SYNOPSIS
.HP
.B XkbColorPtr XkbAddGeomColor
.BI "(\^XkbGeometryPtr " "geom" "\^,"
.BI "char *" "spec" "\^,"
.BI "unsigned int " "pixel" "\^);"
.if n .ti +5n
.if t .ti +.5i
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I \- geom
geometry ta be updated
.TP
.I \- spec
color ta be added
.TP
.I \- pixel
color ta be added
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
Xkb serves up functions ta add a single freshly smoked up element ta tha top-level keyboard 
geometry. In each case tha 
.I num_ * 
fieldz of tha correspondin structure is incremented by 1. These functions do 
not chizzle 
.I sz_* 
unless there is no mo' room up in tha array. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. Some of these functions fill up in tha 
valuez of tha elementz structure from tha arguments, n' you can put dat on yo' toast. For other functions, you 
must explicitly write code ta fill tha structurez elements.

Da top-level geometry description includes a list of 
.I geometry properties. Put ya muthafuckin choppers up if ya feel dis! 
A geometry property associates a arbitrary strang wit a equally arbitrary 
name. Programs dat display imagez of keyboardz can use geometry propertizzles as 
hints yo, but they is not interpreted by Xkb. No other geometry structures refer 
to geometry properties.

.I XkbAddGeomColor 
addz tha specified color 
.I name 
and 
.I pixel 
to tha specified geometry 
.I geom. 
Da top-level geometry description includes a list of up ta MaxColors (32) 
.I color names. 
A color 
.I name 
is a strang whose interpretation aint specified by Xkb n' neither is the
.I pixel 
valuez interpretation. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch fo' realz. All other geometry data structures refer ta flavas rockin 
their indices up in dis global list or pointas ta flavas up in dis list.
.I XkbAddGeomColor 
returns NULL if any of tha parametas is empty or if dat shiznit was not able ta allocate 
space fo' tha color. Shiiit, dis aint no joke. To allocate space fo' a arbitrary number of flavas ta a 
geometry, use tha 
.I XkbAllocGeomColors 
function.
.SH STRUCTURES
.LP
.nf

    typedef struct _XkbColor {
        unsigned int    pixel;      /\(** color */
        char *          spec;       /\(** color name */
    } XkbColorRec,*XkbColorPtr;
    
.fi
